363 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
364 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
365 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
366 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
367 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
368 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
369 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
370 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
371 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
372 // - Misc maths helpers
373 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
374 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
375 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
376 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
377 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }

379 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
380 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return lhs.x*lhs.x + lhs.y*lhs.y; }

387 static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
388 static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }

420 // Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
421 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
422 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
423 {
424  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
425  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
426 
427  ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
428  ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
429  ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
430  ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
431 
432  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
433  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
434  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
435  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
436  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
437  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
438  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
439  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
440  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
441  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
442  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
443  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
444  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
445  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
446  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
447  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
448  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
449  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
450  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
451  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
452  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
453  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
454 };

456 // Helper: ImBitArray
457 inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
458 inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
459 inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
460 inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2)
461 {
462  while (n <= n2)
463  {
464  int a_mod = (n & 31);
465  int b_mod = ((n2 >= n + 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
466  ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
467  arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
468  n = (n + 32) & ~31;
469  }
470 }

472 // Helper: ImBitVector
473 // Store 1-bit per value.
474 struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
475 {
476  ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
477  void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
478  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
479  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
480  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
481  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }

484 // Helper: ImPool<>
485 // Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
486 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
487 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
488 template<typename T>
489 struct IMGUI_API ImPool
490 {
491  ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
492  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
493  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
494 
495  ImPool() { FreeIdx = 0; }
496  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
497  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
498  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
499  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
500  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
501  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
502  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = 0; }
503  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); return &Buf[idx]; }
504  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
505  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); }
506  void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
507  int GetSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
508 };

510 // Helper: ImChunkStream<>
511 // Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
512 // This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
513 // We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries (this what the '(X + 3) & ~3' statement is for)
514 // The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
515 template<typename T>
516 struct IMGUI_API ImChunkStream
517 {
518  ImVector<char> Buf;
519 
520  void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
521  bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
522  int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
523  T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = ((HDR_SZ + sz) + 3u) & ~3u; int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
524  T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
525  T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
526  int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
527  T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
528  int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
529  T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
530 };

1221 // (this is designed to be stored in a ImChunkStream buffer, with the variable-length Name following our structure)
1222 struct ImGuiWindowSettings
1223 {
1224  ImGuiID ID;
1225  ImVec2ih Pos; // NB: Settings position are stored RELATIVE to the viewport! Whereas runtime ones are absolute positions.
1226  ImVec2ih Size;
1227  ImVec2ih ViewportPos;
1228  ImGuiID ViewportId;
1229  ImGuiID DockId; // ID of last known DockNode (even if the DockNode is invisible because it has only 1 active window), or 0 if none.
1230  ImGuiID ClassId; // ID of window class if specified
1231  short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
1232  bool Collapsed;
1233  bool WantApply; // Set when loaded from .ini data (to enable merging/loading .ini data into an already running context)
1234 
1235  ImGuiWindowSettings() { ID = 0; Pos = Size = ViewportPos = ImVec2ih(0, 0); ViewportId = DockId = ClassId = 0; DockOrder = -1; Collapsed = WantApply = false; }
1236  char* GetName() { return (char*)(this + 1); }
1237 };

1246  void (*ReadLineFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, void* entry, const char* line); // Read: Called for every line of text within an ini entry
1247  void (*ApplyAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called after reading (in registration order)
1248  void (*WriteAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, ImGuiTextBuffer* out_buf); // Write: Output every entries into 'out_buf'

2130  // - The DockBuilderXXX functions are designed to _eventually_ become a public API, but it is too early to expose it and guarantee stability.
2131  // - Do not hold on ImGuiDockNode* pointers! They may be invalidated by any split/merge/remove operation and every frame.
2132  // - To create a DockSpace() node, make sure to set the ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace flag when calling DockBuilderAddNode().
2133  // You can create dockspace nodes (attached to a window) _or_ floating nodes (carry its own window) with this API.
2134  // - DockBuilderSplitNode() create 2 child nodes within 1 node. The initial node becomes a parent node.
2135  // - If you intend to split the node immediately after creation using DockBuilderSplitNode(), make sure
2136  // to call DockBuilderSetNodeSize() beforehand. If you don't, the resulting split sizes may not be reliable.
2137  // - Call DockBuilderFinish() after you are done.
